win-80" id="cite_note-Goodwin-80"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Abraham_Lincoln#cite_ref-Goodwin_80-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Abraham_Lincoln#cite_ref-Goodwin_80-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a><a href="./Abraham_Lincoln#cite_ref-Goodwin_80-2"><span class="mw-linkback-text">3 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Goodwin-80" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" id="mwBz8">Goodwin, Doris Kearns (2005-10-25). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=4MS3BQAAQBAJ" id="mwB0A"><i id="mwB0E">Team of Rivals: The Political Genius of Abraham Lincoln</i></a>. Simon and Schuster. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwB0I">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwB0M"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/9780684824901" title="Special:BookSources/9780684824901" id="mwB0Q">9780684824901</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Team+of+Rivals%3A+The+Political+Genius+of+Abraham+Lincoln&amp;rft.pub=Simon+and+Schuster&amp;rft.date=2005-10-25&amp;rft.isbn=9780684824901&amp;rft.aulast=Goodwin&amp;rft.aufirst=Doris+Kearns&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D4MS3BQAAQBAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAbraham+Lincoln" class="Z3988" id="mwB0U"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt2959" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwB0Y"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-Mackubin-81" id="cite_note-Mackubin-81"><a href="./Abraham_Lincoln#cite_ref-Mackubin_81-0" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Mackubin-81" class="m